  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study was to evaluate the potential reorganization in the sensorimotor
      cortex in spinal cord injury (SCI) patients after Body Weight Supported Treadmill Training
      (BWSTT) associated with conventional motor rehabilitation. The investigators hypothesized
      that training with weight bearing associated with conventional motor rehabilitation will be
      able to reorganize the brain.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
