  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with ASIA C or D and the ability to cooperate with instructions of the motor
             task required. The motor task was to perform ankle plantar flexion and toe flexion and
             fingers and thumbs movement of the both sides; they also had to be able to fulfill the
             general conditions necessary for an MRI exploration.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with uncontrollable spasticity-induced body movements were excluded from the
             study.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
